==English==

{{wikipedia}}
===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/wuːt/}}

===Interjection===
'''w00t'''! (''woot!'')
# (''slang'') Used to express [[joy]], particularly due to [[success]] or [[victory]].
# (''initialism'') We [[Own]] the Other Team.

====Usage notes====
It can also stand for "what?" if a question mark is placed after it, as in "Wo0t?."

===Etymology===
Uncertain origin.  Possibly any or all of these:
* an [[initialism]] for We Own the Other Team, or
* an [[onomatopoeia]] of capture sirens from online capture-the-flag games, or
* an [[amalgamation]] of "wow, loot", or
* a [[leetspeak]] mutation of [[woo]], [[what]] or [[root]].
* a mutation of [[root]], a term shouted by [[hackers]] when they reach [[root]] level access of a targeted system

